[[bench]]
name = "benchmarks"
harness = false

[package]
name = "flash-lso"
version = "0.6.0"
authors = [ "CUB3D <callumthom11@gmail.com>",]
description = "Fast and safe SOL/AMF0/AMF3 parsing. Supports serde, Adobe flex and cyclic references"
repository = "https://github.com/CUB3D/rust-sol"
readme = "README.md"
license = "MIT"
keywords = [ "sol", "amf", "parser", "serializer", "flash",]
edition = "2021"
categories = [ "data-structures", "encoding", "parser-implementations",]

[dependencies]
nom = "7.1.3"
enumset = "1.1.5"
thiserror = "2.0.3"

[dev-dependencies]
pretty_assertions = "1.4.0"
serde_json = "1.0.128"
criterion = "0.5.1"

[features]
default = [ "amf3",]
flex = []
serde = [ "dep:serde", "enumset/serde",]
all = [ "serde", "flex",]
amf3 = []

[dependencies.serde]
version = "1.0.210"
optional = true
features = [ "derive", "rc",]

[lints.rust.unexpected_cfgs]
level = "warn"
check-cfg = [ "cfg(fuzzing)",]

[workspace]
resolver = "2"
members = [ "derive",]

[package]
name = "gc-arena"
description = "safe, incrementally garbage collected arenas"
version = "0.5.3"
authors = [ "kyren <catherine@kyju.org>", "moulins", "Aaron Hill <aa1ronham@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2024"
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"

[features]
default = [ "std",]
std = []
tracing = [ "dep:tracing",]
allocator-api2 = [ "dep:allocator-api2", "hashbrown?/allocator-api2",]

[dev-dependencies]
rand = "0.8"
trybuild = "1.0"

[workspace.package]
version = "0.5.3"
authors = [ "kyren <catherine@kyju.org>", "moulins", "Aaron Hill <aa1ronham@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2024"
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"

[dependencies.allocator-api2]
version = "0.2"
optional = true
default-features = false
features = [ "alloc",]

[dependencies.enum-map]
version = "2.7"
optional = true
default-features = false

[dependencies.gc-arena-derive]
path = "./derive"
version = "0.5.3"

[dependencies.hashbrown]
version = "0.16"
optional = true
default-features = false

[dependencies.indexmap]
version = "2.13"
optional = true
default-features = false

[dependencies.slotmap]
version = "1.1"
optional = true
default-features = false

[dependencies.smallvec]
version = "1.15"
optional = true
default-features = false

[dependencies.tracing]
version = "0.1.37"
optional = true
default-features = false

[package]
name = "gc-arena-derive"
description = "proc-macro support for gc-arena"
version = "0.5.3"
authors = [ "kyren <catherine@kyju.org>", "moulins", "Aaron Hill <aa1ronham@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2024"
license = "MIT"
readme = "README.md"
repository = "https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"

[lib]
proc-macro = true

[dependencies]
proc-macro2 = "1.0.56"
quote = "1.0.26"
synstructure = "0.13"

[dependencies.syn]
version = "2.0.17"
features = [ "default", "visit-mut",]

[package]
name = "h263-rs"
version = "0.1.0"
authors = [ "Mike Welsh <mwelsh@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2018"
license = "MIT OR Apache-2.0"

[dependencies]
bitflags = "2.4.0"
thiserror = "2.0.3"
num-traits = "0.2.16"
lazy_static = "1.4.0"

[package]
name = "h263-rs-deblock"
version = "0.1.0"
authors = [ "TÖRÖK Attila <torokati44@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2018"
license = "MIT OR Apache-2.0"

[dependencies]
wide = "0.7.11"
itertools = "0.14.0"

[package]
name = "h263-rs-yuv"
version = "0.1.0"
authors = [ "Mike Welsh <mwelsh@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2018"
license = "MIT OR Apache-2.0"

[dependencies]
wide = "0.7.11"
bytemuck = "1.13.1"

[package]
name = "jpegxr"
version = "0.3.1"
authors = [ "Brooke Vibber <bvibber@pobox.com>",]
edition = "2018"
license = "BSD-3-Clause"
description = "Wrapper for Microsoft's C JPEG XR image codec library"
readme = "readme.md"
homepage = "https://github.com/brion/jpegxr"
repository = "https://github.com/brion/jpegxr.git"
keywords = [ "jxr", "jpegxr", "jpeg-xr",]
categories = [ "multimedia::images",]

[dependencies]
thiserror = "2.0.3"
libc = "0.2.153"

[build-dependencies]
bindgen = "0.70.1"

[build-dependencies.cc]
version = "1.0.83"
features = [ "parallel",]

[package]
name = "nellymoser-rs"
version = "0.1.2"
authors = [ "relrelb <relrelbachar@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2021"
description = "A pure Rust decoder for the Nellymoser audio codec"
license = "MIT"

[dependencies]
bitstream-io = "4"
once_cell = "1.10.0"
rustdct = "0.7.0"

[package]
name = "nihav_codec_support"
version = "0.1.0"
authors = [ "Kostya Shishkov <kostya.shishkov@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2018"

[dependencies.nihav_core]
path = "../nihav-core"

[package]
name = "nihav_duck"
version = "0.1.0"
authors = [ "Kostya Shishkov <kostya.shishkov@gmail.com>",]
edition = "2018"

[dependencies.nihav_core]
path = "../nihav-core"

[dependencies.nihav_codec_support]
path = "../nihav-codec-support"

[package]
name = "regress"
version = "0.10.3"
authors = [ "ridiculousfish <corydoras@ridiculousfish.com>",]
description = "A regular expression engine targeting EcmaScript syntax"
license = "MIT OR Apache-2.0"
repository = "https://github.com/ridiculousfish/regress"
keywords = [ "regex", "regexp",]
edition = "2021"
readme = "README.md"

[workspace]
members = [ "regress-tool", "gen-unicode", ".",]
default-members = [ "regress-tool", ".",]

[features]
default = [ "backend-pikevm", "std",]
std = [ "memchr/std",]
backend-pikevm = []
index-positions = []
prohibit-unsafe = []
utf16 = []

[dependencies]
hashbrown = "0.15.0"

[profile.release]

[dependencies.memchr]
version = "2.4.0"
default-features = false

[source.vendored-sources]
directory = "cargo/vendor"

[source.crates-io]
replace-with = "vendored-sources"

[source."https://github.com/ruffle-rs/rust-flash-lso"]
git = "https://github.com/ruffle-rs/rust-flash-lso"
replace-with = "vendored-sources"
rev = "998f47c926b9986aabd518fbb7394ff56936d0b0"

[source."https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"]
git = "https://github.com/kyren/gc-arena"
replace-with = "vendored-sources"
rev = "75671ae03f53718357b741ed4027560f14e90836"

[source."https://github.com/ruffle-rs/h263-rs"]
git = "https://github.com/ruffle-rs/h263-rs"
replace-with = "vendored-sources"
rev = "b3f905511acc7b80861dac45fdc5ca913b6029e5"

[source."https://github.com/ruffle-rs/jpegxr"]
git = "https://github.com/ruffle-rs/jpegxr"
replace-with = "vendored-sources"
rev = "2a429b0d71ab416e10b73d4dbdcf34cfe2900395"

[source."https://github.com/ruffle-rs/nellymoser"]
git = "https://github.com/ruffle-rs/nellymoser"
replace-with = "vendored-sources"
rev = "073eb48d907201f46dea0c8feb4e8d9a1d92208c"

replace-with = "vendored-sources"
rev = "5fcb02513c5ab4e00df4346459f5a8d0521d8fed"
